1. Install Python

Use the following link to get the step by step guide on how to install Python on Windows: https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/download-and-install-python-3-latest-version/#download-python-on-windows-10
Use the following link to get the step by step guide on how to install Python on macOS: https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/how-to-download-and-install-python-latest-version-on-macos-mac-os-x/
Use the following link to get the step by step guide on how to install Python on Linux: https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/download-and-install-python-3-latest-version/#install-python-on-linux

2. Install pip (a package manager for Python)

Use the following link to install pip: https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/installation/

3. Install Flask

install Flask by running the following command in your terminal:
pip install flask

4. Run the app

Go to your terminal and run the following command:
python index.py

If successful, you will see something like this:

* Running on http://127.0.0.1:8000/ (Press CTRL+C to quit)
